Back then, much of this work sought to contrast self-compassion with self-esteem.
Self-esteem has fallen out of favor, and it is starting to seem these days as if self-compassion is taking its place.
Really, though, self-indifference and self-compassion are just new-fangled terms for an ancient concept: humility.
Really, though, self-indifference and self-compassion are just new-fangled terms for an ancient concept: humility.
This is the great relief of self-indifference, especially for those of us raised in the self-esteem movement.